		<div>That melee-buff idea is interesting.  I dont think it'll work though, because as we know, pure melees are at the bottom end of class desirability.  This buff would simply put clerics down at the bottom for those 2 minutes, obviously you couldnt make them better at melee than the pure melees.<br />
<br />
But, it is an interesting idea.  Brings to mind the druid's situation, having to deal with a community and mindset split 50/50 between healing and nuking.<br />
<br />
Along the lines of your buff idea, though, there's some promise.  Maybe something like Casting Mindsets...  say a caster could change mindsets once an hour or once a day or something... a cleric could enter a combat-cleric mindset for xp-ing or soloing, and be empowered with stronger nukes, maybe killer Slay Undead like proc powers, stuff like that.   If they needed to, they could enter the healing-cleric mindset, which reduces their damage powers and instead gives them full access to all their heals at full or bonus strength, perhaps with a small mana savings or cast time savings.   The neutral mindset would leave them as they are now.<br />
<br />
Could apply something like that to all the casters.  Would definitely make things more interesting, fitting in line with the dev's apparent goal of spicing up the gameplay.</div>
