		<!-- message -->
		<div>Interesting suggestion Wyte. But still shortsighted from my point of view.<br />
<br />
Why should clerics be reduced to being masters of HP healing? There is so much more to flesh out an interesting and demanding healer role. <br />
<br />
Cures for example. Poisen &amp; Disease curing is of no real use in EQ (except on a few special encounters). Why not making both REAL dangers everywhere and forcing a cleric to react quickly if someone got affected? <br />
<br />
All sorts of mind sickness could be another great field of clerical duty as well as protection against mind affecting spells.<br />
<br />
Clerics are worshipping gods, aren't they? Why is there no use of prayers in EQ? For example, giving clerics group supporting prayer chants to use when no heal is needed. (And make them different for each god to add some flavor). This could be a great system to increase usefulness of having more than one cleric in group. <br />
<br />
Current EQ curse system is laughable. Get cursed, get curse cured seconds later. There *could* be so much more game content built around curses (including the need of clerics).<br />
<br />
The whole undead area is a joke as well. Who really fears any undead mob if you lack a cleric or paladin in group? 99% of all undead mobs are not any different from any other random orc pawn. <br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				One answer is: Make the Cleric choose between melee and healer.
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div> <br />
<br />
I don't think clerics should be able to choose. I my vision Clerics should be well armored and equipped for occasionally self defense but not more. Give them more choices in spell casting, than just the repeating task of "Complete Heal, Heal over Time or Fast Heal now?".</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
