	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>There are a few things being discussed here and I thought I'd make it clear that the problem is not just CH, it is Cleric's monopoly on healing.  Right now, CH is the reason for that monopoly, but statements like this<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				Release the death grip Clerics have on healing, balance it out between priests, with Clerics being the definative best class for the job.
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div><br />
<br />
Are seriously misunderstanding the nature of the problem.  Healing, regardless of the form it comes in, is the single most important thing in EQ.  Clerics, Druids and Shaman all need to be essentially equal (equal != identical.  Some could be better in some circumstances and others in others) at healing.  The entire idea that Clerics need to be the best healers needs to be done away with.  Clerics need something else to be really good at.  I still recommend DPS and CC (two things they already have, but need to be better at it), because the path to those qualities is an easy one.  Now, Clerics can still be "the best healers" (and thus weaker than Druids and Shamen in other areas) is "best" means most diverse or means a Cleric bonus on effciency (they have that 5% bonus right now).<br />
<br />
In the end, though, if you make CH less important to the game, but put some other healing neccessity in the game that only Clerics have, you have done nothing.<br />
<br />
Changes that should be made.<br />
<br />
<u>Healing</u> <br />
<br />
Druids:<br />
TR/KR - remove % cap.  KR mana to 400.  TR healing to 3500.  KR healing to 5500.  Make HG work.<br />
<br />
NI - casting time reduced to 3.25<br />
<br />
Add a line of Group TR, KR and NI.<br />
<br />
SotW to 8 ticks and 15 min refresh.<br />
<br />
Shaman:<br />
KM - Remove % cap.  Healing to 3000.  Add an upgrade at 64/65 that heals for 4800.  Still 400 mana.  Make HG work.<br />
<br />
TM - casting time to 3.25<br />
<br />
Add a group version of Quiesence<br />
<br />
Clerics:<br />
CH to 3000 total heal.<br />
<br />
Add two upgrades to CH.  One in the fifties healing 3500 and one in the sixties healing 5500.  Mana cost still 400 on both of them.<br />
<br />
There.  Cleric healing more diverse than everyone elses and slightly better, but each class able to fill in for a Cleric in the healing role on a raid.<br />
<br />
<u>Non-Healing</u><br />
<br />
Druids:<br />
Add some form of Jolt.<br />
<br />
Clerics:<br />
Add a Fire Based line of DDs, with a couple of pillar spells.  Use Druid Fire Nukes as a basis.  Add them a couple levels later and about 10% less damage.  Use druid out-door only Pillar spells as basis for Cleric Fire Pillars - same deal - get them later, about 20% less damage, no outdoor only restriction.<br />
<br />
Tweak by a little bit the recast time on Cleric Magic Based nukes.<br />
<br />
Add a line of PBAE stuns.<br />
<br />
Add a line of Pillar stuns.  <br />
<br />
IMO - fixed.  All preists can heal at raids, though Clerics can fill the most roles when doing so and are slightly better at it.  Clerics can now add real DPS to groups and have some soloing abilities and with the right equipment, could even quad.  The stuns add some flexibility to their already pretty good CC.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
